        "committer": {
          "name": "Hongchao Zhang",
          "email": "hongchao.zhang@intel.com",
          "date": "2018-05-24 20:09:27.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "BGI-86 lwp: fix lwp reconnection issue",
        "message": "BGI-86 lwp: fix lwp reconnection issue\n\nAfter the OST or MDT was restarted, the lwp reconnection can be\nfailed for -EALREADY because the connect count in the connecttion\nrequest is less then the value saved in the corresponding export\nat MDT0000, which could cause the system hang.\n\nThe patch also changes lustre_lwp_connect to use OBD_CONNECT_MDS_MDS\nflag only when the connection is between MDTs.\n\nChange-Id: I031e3940ce786178f0d9a6ab4e261033b7d8e29e\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
